entries.s_10: Ah, peaceful quiet. How I love it. You're the one who got rid of the flewts. The evil, noisy flewts. Did you want something?
entries.s_14: And now you're yammering. It just gets worse and worse.
entries.s_15: Those darn flewts are back! Arrgh!!
entries.s_16: Do you have a security beacon from Stonewall Labs?
entries.s_17: Yes. Yes I do. Well, no actually I don't. I buried it. I was hoping it would grow into a beacon tree. So far, nothing, but I haven't given up hope. It's only been a few years. I still think it'll sprout into something.
entries.s_20: I know you're hungry. I know! Now be quiet about it. Darn flewts.
entries.s_43: I can't hear anything over those flewts. Darn starving flewts won't be quiet about how hungry they are.
entries.s_56: I can't talk with these starving flewts all over the place! They won't stop yammering about how hungry they are.
